body:
I am trying to make a slide show by reactjs. In the slide show the next button work perfectly but the previous button have problem.
You can show demo [here](https://jsfiddle.net/69z2wepo/125390/).

The next button handler works perfectly and the prev button handler  works perfectly until the slide don't arrive to first of array.When the slide arrive to first of array the slide show does not work perfectly.
please help me to solve this problem.
my state and functions :
```
state = {
    current: 2,
    numbers:[1,2,3,4,5 ]
  }
  checkIndex = ( index ) => {
    if ( index < 0 ) return 0;
    if ( index > 4 ) return 4;
    return index;
  }
```
next button handler:

```
  onNextHandler = () => {
    let currentIndex = this.state.current;
    let nextIndex = this.checkIndex( currentIndex + 1 );
    let numbers=[ ...this.state.numbers ];
    if ( nextIndex === numbers.length-1 ) {
      const first_num = numbers[ 0 ];
      numbers.splice( 0, 1 );
      numbers.splice( numbers.length, 0, first_num );
      nextIndex--;
    }
    this.setState( { numbers, current:nextIndex } );
  }
```
pre next button handler:
```
 onPrevHandler = () => {
    let currentIndex = this.state.current;
    let prevIndex = this.checkIndex( currentIndex - 1 );
    let numbers=[ ...this.state.numbers ];
    if ( prevIndex === 0 ) {
      const last_num = numbers[  numbers.length - 1  ];
      numbers.splice( numbers.length-1, 1 );
      numbers.splice( 0, 0, last_num );
      prevIndex++;
    }
    this.setState( { numbers,current:prevIndex } );
  };
```

on render function i map each array to list element like below.

  ```
 render () {
    let numsList = this.state.numbers.map( ( num, index ) => {
      console.log(index,this.state.current)
      if ( index < this.state.current ) {
        return <li key={ num } value={ num } className="before">{ num }</li>
      } else if ( index > this.state.current ) {
        return <li key={ num } value={ num } className="after">{ num }</li>
      } else {
        return <li key={ num } value={ num } className="current">{ num }</li>
      }
    } );
    return (
      <div className="App">
        <div>
          <ul>
            { numsList}
            <div className="pick-arw pick-arw-l"
              onClick={ this.onPrevHandler }
            >{ "<" }</div>
            <div
              className="pick-arw pick-arw-r"
              onClick={ this.onNextHandler } >{ ">" }</div>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  }
```
